rounds.event: For the first time in history, all five major storm surge gates in the Netherlands are closed simultaneously in the wake of a storm.
The first block of the blockchain of the decentralized payment system Bitcoin, called the Genesis block, is established by the creator of the system, Satoshi Nakamoto.
deaths: Betty Freeman, American philanthropist and photographer

rounds.event: Proceedings of the U.S. Congress are televised for the first time.
Over 640 are killed after a magnitude 6.4 earthquake strikes the Mexican states Puebla and Veracruz.
births: Siegfried Buback, German lawyer and politician, Attorney General of Germany

rounds.event: A gun battle in the East End of London leaves two dead. It sparked a political row over the involvement of then-Home Secretary Winston Churchill.
deaths: Alexandros Papadiamantis, Greek author and poet
